      <h1 class='title'>Northern Ireland Forest Service</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 14 October 2003 vol 411 c2WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_2ws' title='Col. 2WS &mdash; HC Deb 14 October 2003 vol 411 c2WS' name='column_2ws' href='#column_2ws' rel='bookmark'>2WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0411P0_20031014_CWS_5'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-ian-pearson' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0411P0_20031014_CWS_5' title='Link to this speech by Mr Ian Pearson' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-ian-pearson" title="Mr Ian Pearson">The Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Northern Ireland (Mr. Ian Pearson)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">The Key Targets for achievement by the Northern Ireland Forest Service (an Executive Agency of the Department of Agriculture and Rural Development) in 2003&#x2013;4 are<q>To publish a statement on forest policy and develop a strategy for implementing the policy.</q>
          <q>To establish 500 hectares of new plantations.</q>
          <q>To replant 750 hectares of land following harvesting.</q>
          <q>To pay out woodland grant scheme and farm woodland premium scheme grants of &#x00A3;1.8 million to encourage the extension of the area of private woodland.</q>
          <q>To pay 90 per cent. of woodland grant scheme and farm woodland premium scheme claims within eight weeks of receipt of a properly completed claim form.</q>
          <q>To retain certification under the UK woodland assurance standard</q>
          <q>To produce 400,000m<sup>3</sup> of timber for sale to the wood processing sector.</q>
          <q>To achieve 400,000 paying visitors to forests.</q>
          </p><p>The Forest Service business plan for 2003&#x2013;4 will be published and placed in the Libraries of both Houses at a later date.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
